social_posts.post_text: As always, my top nine has nothing to do with the number of likes my photos got. These photos are what meant something to me this year- I traveled to six out of seven continents (thank you dearly to @myvacaya!!!) and performed on three of them, bought a house, performed at @radiocitymusichall, tried new things onstage, grew as a singer thanks to @mattfarnsworthvoice, shared eccentric and memorable moments with my family, shared the stage with wonderful friends like @jasminericenyc and @thelittlemermen, was one of the first drag queens to ever step foot on the continent of Antarctica, got to be in a National ad campaign for @tacobell … these are only a couple of the amazing things that this year brought, and it’s easy to forget just how many there were until I list them all out. I’ve got my resolutions for the new year, and I’m not going to share them, but for today I’m celebrating the ones that came true. Happy 2023! I hope you’ve got big plans, and I hope you’ll chase them past January ❤️❤️❤️

LA friends, what are you doing next Wednesday? I think you should come see me and @missipyle at @dynastytypewriter, cause it’s gonna be a fucking amazing show. Here’s a little blurb if you needed a good reason!

"The world is in chaos with drag bans, trans bans, and threats to women’s rights, what's a girl and her drag queen to do? Actress Missi Pyle and drag queen Pissi Myles, when faced with JUST THIS QUESTION, realized that their only options were to do a high dive off of a high bridge, or brush off their knees, pull the gum out of their hair, and save the world themselves with comedy, music, and audience play. It is your civic duty to attend this show and save America from impending doom!”

Tickets are $20 in advance, $25 at the door, so get ‘em now at DynastyTypewriter.com and help us save the world!

No matter how many times you see your name on a marquis, it just never gets old. Especially when you get to see it next to the name of an amazing friend like @missipyle ❤️❤️❤️ that was one for the books, LA! Thank you so much to the fab folks at @dynastytypewriter for having us!!!

Home update- Since @davidayllon and I moved into our house almost six months ago we have had a hard time nesting. Money was tight (cause we just bought a MOTHER****ING HOUSE), and buying the house didn’t mean we were less busy with work, which, for me, meant traveling to about six different countries and three continents (thank you @myvacaya!), working across the country, and working to produce new shows and material.

It has been difficult, and at times upsetting that we have not been able to start to make this house ours, but with the help of Julie Lockwood this past weekend I was able to start the process! She helped me clean out our flower beds and plant new gorgeous plants and flowers that have space (and time) to grow into a gorgeous new addition to our home. today I added some hanging pots to the porch, and I’m so excited to watch them blossom!

And as a treat to myself I got a second yard statue (my first one was a ghostface who lives on my porch, thank you @sb.baxter and @srblomquist!). He does not have a name, but I am looking forward to making him seasonal outfits.

New piano video!

I was inspired to record this because I’ve been listening to the live recording with Elton and George Michael a lot recently. I listen to @eltonjohn a lot- his music really inspires me in such a profound way. It makes me want to create, to learn, and to be better all the time.

This is a very simplified version of the song, I still wouldn’t consider myself a crazy intermediate player, but I’m loving it. So I’m posting this, even with the couple small mistakes it has, because it brings me joy. I hope it does for you, too.

What a joy to get to join @rachelmalak13 and @chrisbohinski on @palivewbre to promote “This Time: A Queer Cabaret”! Rachel and I even coordinated outfits, I hope you were able to tell us apart 😳 check out my appearance, and see you at The People’s Security Bank Theater this Thurs/Fri/Sat for the show! And don’t forget @scrantonfringe’s unbelievable production of George Orwell’s 1984 next week 😊😊😊

Friends, I’m so excited to let you know that I’ll be Starring in “Forever After” at the @thefleatheater in NYC with @tososnyc! This is a super funny and poignant play about queer love (and how it goes right… and wrong), and I’ll be playing Thalia, the muse of comedy from August 12-26!!!! Get your tix at the link in my bio. See you there!
Come see my dressing room at @thefleatheater where I’m starring in Forever After!!! We open tomorrow (8/12), tix available at the link in my bio 😊😊😊

Should I have warned them that I took a #dump in my dressing room? 🤪🤪🤪 to say that this experience was a joy would be an understatement. So rarely do you get to do an amazing show with an amazing cast, an amazing company, an amazing theater, for amazing crowds. This show is easily one of the highlights of my career, and has led to friendships and memories that will be forever cherished. Sad to see it go, but excited to see what will be next ❤️❤️❤️❤️

There is no cut-and-dry answer to what is going on, but my commitment to opposing anti-semitism is unwavering. I am a peaceful person, and will always advocate for peace for all of those effected by terrorism and violence ❤️❤️❤️
